## Update a plan for a sub account

Update a plan for a sub account of the master account on Zoom.

<aside class="notice">Only for the sub account which is a paid account and paid by master account.</aside>

<aside class="notice">Could update a base plan or an additional plan.</aside>

> Definition

```shell
POST <%= config[:api_host] %>ma/account/plan/update
```

```javascript
Zoom.account.planUpdate();
```

> Example Request

```shell
$ curl <%= config[:api_host] %>ma/account/plan/update \
    -X POST \
    -d api_key=<%= config[:ex_api_key] %> \
    -d api_secret=<%= config[:ex_api_secret] %> \
    -d account_id=<%= config[:ex_uuid] %> \
    -d type=1 \
    -d plan="yearly"
```

```javascript
<%= config[:ex_node_init] %>

var account = {
    account_id: "<%= config[:ex_uuid] %>",
    type: 1,
    plan: "monthly"
}

Zoom.account.planUpdate(account, <%= config[:ex_node_res] %>);
```

> Example Response

```json
{
  "id": "w40hUJRpRmmkx4uPXczdHg",
  "updated_at": "2012-11-25T12:00:00Z"
}
```

Arguments | &nbsp;
--- | ---
account_id **required** | The sub account ID.
type **required** | Plan Type. 1 means Base Plan, 2 means Additional Plan. *Default: 1*
plan **required** | A Base Plan or an Additional Plan. See [Plans](#plans) for more details